<section xml:id="sec-missing-values">
  <title>Missing Values</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      This section addresses the common challenge of missing data, including how to identify, understand, and handle missing values.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>Understand different types of missing data</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Learn strategies for handling missing values</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Make informed decisions about missing data treatment</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-types-of-missing-data">
    <title>Types of Missing Data</title>
    <p>
      Missing data can occur for different reasons: Missing Completely at Random (MCAR), Missing at Random (MAR), or Missing Not at Random (MNAR). Understanding the type affects how we handle it.
    </p>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-handling-missing-values">
    <title>Strategies for Handling Missing Values</title>
    <p>
      Options include deletion (listwise or pairwise), imputation (mean, median, or more sophisticated methods), and using methods that can handle missing data directly.
    </p>
  </subsection>

</section>
